comments.content: Artist alter ego name corroborated by The Chicago Defender 15 July 1939, 24
Artist alter ego name corroborated by The Chicago Defender 15 July 1939, 24

"Sunday night concluded a long term stand for Valda Grays' [sic] Show which for the past number of years has been produced by the very capable Valda Gray, the Valda Gray show will open at the quite popular Ritz Lounge"
She used as gender pronoun (and no indication of her being a female impersonator...?).
"Valda Gray, once more excels in the masterful presentation of 'her' latest floor show 'Swingin' at the Cabin Inn' which features those famous impersonators."
One of "leading impersonators" of the city.
"female impersonator and producer of the show"
"has a flare of finales at the Cabin Inn"
"talented female impersonator, has surpassed 'her' previous record as a producer."
Only called White here but Alice White is corroborated in The Chicago Defender 26 Aug 1939, 21.
"featured in a torrid scene, 'Turn On That Red Hot Heat'"
"sings the blues you like to hear"
"sings the songs that make you swoon"
